<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="96" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,1439,1610]" box="[136,364,1439,1466]" pageId="3" pageNumber="96">
<heading bold="true" box="[136,364,1439,1466]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="3" pageNumber="96" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,364,1439,1466]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="96">Conservation status</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,1439,1610]" pageId="3" pageNumber="96">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Demir, Sefali &amp; Yapar" authorityYear="2022" box="[136,351,1476,1501]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Pastinaca" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="96" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vanensis">
<emphasis box="[136,351,1476,1501]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="96">Pastinaca vanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a new species, known only from the 
<typeStatus box="[794,842,1476,1502]" pageId="3" pageNumber="96">type</typeStatus>
locality (Ispiriz mountain), with an area of occupancy of less than 
<quantity box="[273,344,1511,1538]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="96" unit="km" value="10.0">10 km</quantity>
<superScript attach="left" box="[344,352,1511,1525]" fontSize="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="96">2</superScript>
and a number of mature individuals fewer than 250 (about 50). This species can also be found in near places. In this regard, more field observation is needed to determine the conservation status of the plant. Therefore, according to 
<bibRefCitation author="IUCN" box="[282,435,1584,1610]" pageId="3" pageNumber="96" refId="ref2995" refString="IUCN (2019) Guidelines for using the IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria. Ver. 14. Prepared by the Standards and Petitions Subcommittee. Available from: http: // www. iucnredlist. org / documents / RedListGuidelines. pdf (Accessed January 2022)." type="book" year="2019">IUCN (2019)</bibRefCitation>
, the new species should be regarded as DD (Data Deficient) category.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
